    "updated_at": "2025-09-29T16:37:38Z",
    "body": "1. The install script allows overrides for platform detection including `PLATFORM`, which some embedded Linux systems set to unexpected values which can lead to issues in the install script (e.g. certain NAS systems).\n2. Windows CI fails due to an unrelated issue (https://github.com/starship/starship/pull/6993).\n3. As far as I can also tell the existing use of `tr` is in line with POSIX standards so I am surprised this is causing issues.",
